# Resume Keyword Checker

The Resume Keyword Checker is a simple web application built with Python and Flask that allows users to upload resumes and check for specific keywords within those resumes. Resumes are processed and categorized as either successful (containing keywords) or failed (not containing keywords). This project is useful for HR departments and recruitment teams to streamline the resume screening process.

## Features

- Upload one or multiple resumes at a time.
- Specify keywords for resume scanning.
- Automatically categorize resumes as successful or failed.
- Display the number of resumes processed successfully.

## Prerequisites

Before you start, make sure you have the following requirements installed:

- Python
- Flask
- pdfplumber

You can install the required packages using pip:

```bash
pip install Flask pdfplumber


How to Use
Clone the repository to your local machine:
bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/your-username/resume-keyword-checker.git
Navigate to the project directory:
bash
Copy code
cd resume-keyword-checker
Run the Flask application:
bash
Copy code
python app.py
Open your web browser and go to http://127.0.0.1:5000/.

Use the web interface to upload resumes and specify keywords.

The application will categorize the resumes and provide feedback on the number of resumes processed successfully.

Project Structure
The project is organized as follows:

app.py: The main Flask application.
templates/index.html: The HTML template for the web interface.
uploads/: A folder to store uploaded resumes.
successful_resumes/: A folder to store resumes with matching keywords.
failed_resumes/: A folder to store resumes without matching keywords.
styles.css: The CSS file for styling the web interface.

Contributing
Feel free to contribute to this project by creating issues, proposing enhancements, or submitting pull requests.
